node.text: As #pridemonth comes to a close, @molleegray and @kent_boyd of @pridehousela, “Dance Moms” alum @zackery_torres, and “RuPaul’s Drag Race” alum and drag queen @kimchi_chic share the best things about being LGBTQ+ in 2021 as well as some words of wisdom for young queer people. 🌈 Share what being LBGTQ+ means to you in the comments! 👇✨ #pride

node.title: The Best Part About Being LGBTQ+ In 2021

node.text:
Coming out is a personal journey that looks different for everyone. We asked @jekajane, @molleegray, and @kent_boyd of @pridehousela, “Dance Moms” alum @zackery_torres, and “RuPaul’s Drag Race” alum and drag queen @kimchi_chic their advice on coming out, so if you’re not sure where to start, they have you covered. ❤️

Stay tuned for more #pride education and celebration to take with you for the rest of  #pridemonth and beyond! 🌈💗

node.title: Coming Out Advice | Pride Month | Seventeen

We asked @jekajane, @molleegray, and @kent_boyd of @pridehousela, “Dance Moms” alum @zackery_torres, and “RuPaul’s Drag Race” alum and drag queen @kimchi_chic to tell us what pride means to them, and what they had to say is *so* inspiring. ✨ 

Stay tuned for more #pride education and celebration to take with you for the rest of  #pridemonth and beyond! 🌈💗

node.title: What Does Pride Mean to You? | Pride Month | Seventeen

node.text:
At 13, @ashlynso_ is proving that activism has no age limit. As an accomplished fashion designer and accidental activist, she’s using her voice to stand up against AAPI hate. 

We asked Ashlyn to share her experience as an Asian American, what makes the AAPI community so special, and much more. #aapiheritagemonth #haapihour

node.title: Fashion Designer & Accidental Activist Ashlyn So On Her AAPI Experience

node.text: Whether you've just started the new school year or you're counting down the days, it's completely normal if you're feeling some back-to-school anxiety. Save this for when you need a little extra help and head to the link in bio for more info ❤️.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Seventeen on August 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'seventeen BEST. YEAR. YET. 6 TIPS TO HELP YOU COMBAT SCHOOL ANXIETY'.

Photo by Seventeen on August 10, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says '01 WRITE DOWN HOW YOU'RE FEELING. Make a list of fears and anxieties to get them out of your head. This will help you make a plan to tackle them head on.'.

Photo by Seventeen on August 10, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says '02 PREPARE FOR YOUR FIRST DAY IN ADVANCE. Pick out your outfit, pack your bag, and es a routine so you have to worry about logistics.'.

Photo by Seventeen on August 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says '03 TALK TO SOMEONE. Chances are your friends are feeling the same way. Talking things out with them or your parents can help you feel more able to handle your anxieties You can also use apps like BetterHelp and Sanvello to seek professional help from a therapist or counselor if needed.'.

Photo by Seventeen on August 10, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says '04 REACH OUT TO YOUR TEACHERS. If you already know your teachers, contact them before school starts to introduce yourself. This means on your first day, you'll already have a relationship with them.'.

Photo by Seventeen on August 10, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says '05 REMIND YOURSELF OF THE GOOD THINGS. You've been to school before! Remember the good things you loved about it and the things you will be returning to, like sports teams, after school activities, and lunchtime chats.'.

Photo by Seventeen on August 10, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says '06 REMEMBER, YOU AREN'T ALONE. It's easy to feel like you're facing the world (or, in this case, school) solo, but you aren't. All of your classmates are in the same position as you are and, most likely, have the same fears.'.
Photo shared by Seventeen on August 09, 2021 tagging @bellahadid. May be an image of 1 person.
